<br>
Only aout 28 tagged members went, including 6 as alternate characters.  Another guild that has members that raids with us at times brought a bunch of people.  People brought friends.  People brought friends of friends.  Some random people were in the right zone at the right time.<br>
<br>
It ended up being about 106 people and the scary thing is the raid went pretty smooth from beginning to end.  People seemed to have a good time and though I did not even know about half the raid they all seemed to listen and follow directions well.  The result is a lot of new people are flagged for HoH now and can xp there if they like.  No real harm in that.<br>
