<br>
I also think he goes a little overboard drawing connections between FoH raiding with 40+ and other people raiding with 95.  This game is really not that hard, and never has been.  It takes teamwork and coordination, and figuring out tactics adds depth, but any PvPer will eagerly explain how shallow the PvE game really is.  Given time, these mobs are going to die whether people bring 30 or bring 120.  What puts guilds real top guilds ahead of everyone else is their ability to kill stuff first, better, and faster.  That is how it has always been.<br>
<br>
Those top guilds accomplish what they do because of leadership, teamwork, dedication, skill, and a drive to be the best.  The guilds that follow usually have the same in different degrees.  Some have the drive but not the leadership, some have the leadership but not the drive...  etc etc it's different in every collection of people.  And many of those guilds, while they have leadership, teamwork, dedication, skill, and a drive to succeed, also care about things other than tangible feats and accomplishments.<br>
<br>
