<br>
So, beside the soloers who will have a harder time competing with groups for solo spots (cry me a river), there's no real downside to having more people flagged for tier3 zones, not like HoH is lacking mobs anyway.<br>
<br>
And it's not like those pickup raids will make it to tier4 anytime soon. IMHO tier 1-3 are the ones casual players should have access to, leaving tier4 and plane of time for the ubers to play with. <br>
<br>
I have nothing agaisnt pickup zerg rush on AD, behemoth, grummus, TT, etc. and I don't think a zerg rush would allow them to get flagged for and kill rallos, so all seems fine in my mind. Truely PoP seems to be the best designed expansion yet. Ubers have burned through the first 3 tiers pretty fast, leaving them behind for the more casual players to play in. Both the casual and the ubers have their playground, both have &quot;boss&quot; mobs available to kill in their respective tiers, how many zerg they need is irrelevant, they both get to kill what they like. While the ubers are trowing 40-50 at fennin, the casual are trowing 100 at aerin dar. I still don't see why it pisses off people...<br>
<br>
To those complaining, if it pisses you off that &quot;newbies&quot; have access to your zone, how about you move to higher end zone where they won't reach you for at least a few other months? (don't think any casual player will be flagged for sol ro soon for example, and that's not even tier 4).<br>
<br>
So once again, grats to the newly HoH flagged people on 7th, watch out for blowing trials for no reason please, we sometime do them to flag the slackass in the guild. Beside that, more power to you and have fun, I'll be somewhere where I won't be bothered by you anyway, heck I might even pop in and group with you on a slow day, who knows? ^_^ <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=75721">Woon</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->  <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://tde.e-slackers.net/">&lt;TDE&gt;</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <br>
