</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cicelygoldenfair>cicely goldenfair</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 461<br> <font color=#333333>(1/28/03 2:15:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8571.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Re:</span><hr size=1> it is always more fun to do more with less.  today, for example, i participated in a 12 person dozekar kill.  flawless, at that.  everyone was skilled, we knew each other, we had trust in each other, and it was a very memorable encounter.  in fact, it was the second most memorable dozekar encounter i have experienced... the first being the first one, where we had only like 31 guild members, we felt very understaffed, and yet we somehow did what (at the time) we felt was 'impossible' for us.<br>
<br>
on the same note, however, the flag system in planes of power is designed to progress via killing uber named mobs.  verant places no max list on the amount of people that can kill some of these mobs; hence, you see these large raid attempts at the encounter.  if verant would limit the amount that can be flagged (i.e. the three group hedge quest to get flagged for ponb), then that would remove the 120 man encouters.  but until that happens, then there is not many choices for those 120 players but to get together and get their flag.<br>
<br>
it is far easier to participate in a 120 man behemoth encounter to get your potactics flag via sheer brute force than it is to do the podisease quest by finding these very rare drops off of rare mobs to gain entrance into codecay.  if verant had a bit more achievable quests in the game to enter into tier2 and tier3 zones, then you probably won't see 120 man raids.  as it stands, though, verant has neither place a limit on these encounters or implemented attainable and achievable quests that can be done by those in non-high end raid guilds.<br>
<br>
limit the amount of people you can bring to an encounter like you do the ponb flag quest.  implement quests that allows the casual gamer in the casual guild to complete to allow entrance into tier2 and tier3 zones.  doing these two things removes the 120 man raid to get the flag.  imho...<br>
